           🗺️ View by State    📊 Historical Trends
           🔍 Explain Changes   💬 Provide Feedback
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
```

**"Explain Changes" View:**

```
Why did Trust (I) increase by 0.02 this month?

Based on GlassBox AI analysis of 47,382 data points:

┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ Primary Factors (85% of change):                           │
│                                                             │
│  ✓ ACD Pilot States (40%)                                 │
│    Trust increased in [State A], [State B], [State C]      │
│    where American Civic Dividend launched. 2.1M citizens   │
│    participated, creating positive government interactions.│
│                                                             │
│  ✓ Transparency Dashboard Launch (30%)                    │
│    This dashboard itself! Early users (5M unique visitors) │
│    report feeling "more informed about government" in      │
│    surveys, driving trust gains.                           │
│                                                             │
│  ✓ Federal Program Performance (15%)                      │
│    Social Security payments processed 99.2% on-time        │
│    (up from 94%), Veterans Affairs wait times down 18%.   │
│                                                             │
│ Secondary Factors (15% of change):                         │
│  • Reduced partisan conflict in Congress                   │
│  • Positive news coverage of infrastructure projects       │
│                                                             │
